line_1: They'll talk o' patronage an' priests,
line_2: Wi' kindling fury i' their breasts,

line_1: The golden altar, with attending priests,
line_2: Their sacred pomp, and instituted vests.

line_1: You've fought with Men, you never fought with Priests.
line_2: Pardon the Poet all your Wars are Jests,

line_1: Like Thyrsi born by Bacchus ancient Priests.
line_2: Now round its Pole the spiral Hop entwists,
